rComments: I had him for Western literature years ago, and he was very passionate about each work we studied. His lecture style is very calm, and open. He is a joy to listen to. His marking is fair, and often encouraging. His comments were extensive, and the constructive feedback always very helpful. You can tell that he really enjoys teaching.

He was very interested in the texts of study and so it was difficult to not share his enthusiasm.  His reading list for this course was awesome and so interesting.  I had him in my first year, quite awhile ago now, but he definitely got me passionate about so many novels!
Maybe Im mad because he hated my essays but he could never explain why he gave me two Cs on my essays by the time the exam came i just didnt care anymore.

A professor who clearly has tons of passion for literature and the love of fictional characters. His passion is infectious and you can hear it in his voice. Wonderful lectures. A lot of reading, but a fair marker.
He really sets the bar high, and of course that really pushes you to reach your full potential.  A truly great professor who obviously loves literature.  His love of the written word is infectious.
Very interesting class, tough but fair marking
four years after and he's still the best prof i've had. take the course, put some thought into your work, and he'll reward you. and a genuinely nice guy to boot.
Compassionate, smart, inspirational. Born to teach.
Kerslake is the most difficult professor I've faced all year.  Incredibly brilliant and expects us to be as well.  Heavy workload but ultimately very rewarding.
Kerslake is full of himself. Despite his obvious intelligence, his lack of socialibility makes him one of the most intolerable shmucks ever to walk the campus.

He's very insightful and his lectures are almost always worth going to, but he can be a bit dismissive of others' opinions (not just the students, but also other scholars) and wants us to follow HIS exact line of thinking and analysis.
He put 12 texts on the syllabus to be read in 8 months. Engaging class discussions. Very critical in marking.
His sensitivity towards language is rivaled only by his concern for his students
One of the best, if not the best.
my fav prof of the year; hard marker
Has a knack for remembering students!  It's great how he praises his wife!
